				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13008397#post-4521385</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13008397/scp-4768#post-4521385</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 27 Feb 2020 21:28:40 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Shaggydredlocks</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1722371</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Doesn't really do much for me, essentially being an obligatory scp file on a preexisting character &#8212; it's only just above the level of a second hub.</p> <p>This is especially evident in the final addenda which link various stories. Pacing-wise, it just sort-of&#8230;trails off. To that end, I feel an improvement would be to recontextualize the discovery/interview/note from the Donk such that it could come at the end &#8212; as I think it would make for a much stronger point to close on in a narrative sense.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
